    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-30T12:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-30T12:29:00-05:00" n="142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.13/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-30T21:00:00+03:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 1, 7.20 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1685. Minister for Foreign Affairs who just left Embassy tells me death penalty
                    restored in ranks by Council of Ministers and will <pb facs="0254" n="180"
                        xml:id="pg_180"/> be promulgated soon. This shows response to my suggestion
                    that Government should now adopt firmer policy in regard to army discipline and
                    extreme socialism which advocates peace and thereby making more difficult
                    vigorous war prosecution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
